PostgreSQL migration scripts managed by Alembic.

These migrations apply to the PostgreSQL backend only.
SQLite remains the default runtime backend and is not managed by Alembic.

PostgreSQL is not yet wired into create_storage() and is for development/
evaluation use only at this stage.

Apply migrations against a dedicated non-production database:

    KB_AUDIT_POSTGRES_URL=postgresql://localhost/kbaudit \
        alembic upgrade head

Roll back the most recent migration:

    KB_AUDIT_POSTGRES_URL=postgresql://localhost/kbaudit \
        alembic downgrade -1

See alembic.ini at the project root for configuration options.
